White Knights Strike a Telling Blow and Successfully Apprehend the Last Sangvis Ferri Remnants!
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

All this time, the remnants of Sangvis Ferri have tried to destroy Griffin City. Ever since taking office, Prime Minister Dorothy has devoted her efforts to ending this menace, and ten minutes before our submission deadline, we have learned that decisive progress has been made toward this goal.

"We have successfully captured the last Sangvis Ferri ringleader and Sangvis Ferri forces have been utterly crushed," said Captain Jericho of the White Knights' elite Blitzkrieg unit during an interview. "Soon, we will be able to use Architect to pinpoint the location of the Sangvis Ferri Mastermind, so please be at ease, everyone." However, Captain Jericho refused to reveal further information or evidence.

While this news is definitely worth rejoicing over, has Sangvis Ferri ever existed? Many dolls in Griffin City have their doubts on the issue.


...

"...Commander, we've suddenly received a news push notification... Griffin City? White Knights? What are those? Is someone writing a story? Or is this somebody's prank?"

name: The Griffin City Guide to Life on the Southern Hemisphere - the VA11 Hall-A Bar
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

Still complaining about the boring life in Griffin City and only able to make friends with vending machines? Then you should know more about the VA-11-Hall-A Bar. Though it's tucked away in an inconspicuous alley and it constantly smells of strange cleaning solutions, anyone will be deeply enthralled by its atmosphere once you find it and go inside.

The bar's owner (Jill) is quite a positive person and always full of insights about life. You can tell her your deepest worries without having to worry about them making the papers the next day. If your heart is full of things that you just can't pour out anywhere else, then VA-11's repertoire of drinks from the light and pleasing Sugar Rush to the Gut Punch that'll make you give thanks for your life is waiting for you.

It should be noted that if the sole bartender (Gillian) is actually doing her job properly, then the boss Jill would not be making drinks for people behind the counter. Jill dislikes people asking her about that.

name: Great Disturbance Breaks Out At Protest, Vanished Person Returns To Scare Off Prime Minister!
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

After several demonstrations by furious citizens, Prime Minister Dorothy finally decided to give an interview regarding the abnormal "sand rain" weather that has lasted for the past three years. During the course of the interview, a native of our city who had once been confirmed missing showed up, and used illegal means to control former Griffin Dolls into launching a terror attack. Prime Minister Dorothy fled into the Zaibatsu Corporation building, and the exact number of casualties is still being tallied.
The native who caused this public disorder has been confirmed as Stella Hoshii, once the wealthiest resident of Griffin City, but we are currently unable to determine whether she actually employed the legendary Parapluie virus in her actions.
The unrest is still ongoing as of our submission deadline, and we will continue to monitor the situation's development.

name: White Knights Suddenly Turn Traitor, Prime Minister Dorothy Goes Missing!
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

A short while ago, our reporters received news that an abnormal situation has suddenly arisen in the White Knights' base. According to base personnel, all the White Knights inside the base have gone berserk, while the locations of Griffin City's Prime Minister Dorothy, the instigator of the disturbance Stella Hoshii, and Captain Jericho of the White Knights are all currently unknown. The government has not issued any statements so far.
The unrest has spread throughout the city and we humbly urge all citizens to take care when stepping outside, and to be prepared for anything regardless if one is indoors or outdoors.


...

"Commander, this is the fourth piece of weird news we've received today, and we can't find the sender at all… Who could have sent it?"
"In any case, I've contacted 16Lab and asked them to look into this matter as per your orders. I'm sure we'll get the results soon!"

name: Elite White Knight Captain Rescued, Prime Minister Dorothy Makes Appearance Again
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

The disturbance from earlier today is still ongoing. However, according to the latest news from our reporters, the White Knight Captain Jericho has been successfully rescued, with Grand Slam superstar Dana Zane and the long-missing hacker Alma Armas taking part in the rescue. Captain Jericho is currently organizing a counterattack against the berserk White Knight mechs and the chaotic situation is swiftly coming under control. 

Citizens on the scene have also reported witnessing Prime Minister Dorothy and Stella Hoshii, formerly the wealthiest native of this city, returning to the square under the protection of the White Knights to give a speech. "I've decided to follow Prime Minister Dorothy for life, and I won't miss a single piece of Prime Minister Dorothy's merchandise, her autographs and her handshake vouchers!" said a citizen/bodyguard who saw Prime Minister Dorothy at the scene.

name: VA11 Hall-A Bar Employees Actually Accomplices In The Rebellion!?
content:
Author: Lana Smithee
The White Knight Rebellion has gradually calmed down, but the official statement on the matter is quite surprising. The government has announced that the operator of the VA-11 Hall-A bar Julianne Stingray (AKA Jill) and the bartender she employed called Gillian (alias of our former reporter Gr G28) were responsible for sheltering the mastermind behind this rebellion, "Anna Graem". The Augmented Eye has always insisted on providing accurate and high-quality reporting to our readers and we severely condemn the position assumed by the government's media messaging. In addition, Gr G28 has already resigned from our paper and The Augmented Eye takes no responsibility for her actions or statements.

—You all know what's going on already, there were so many people there and everyone saw it! If you want to ignore the facts then go right ahead, Chief Editor, I know that the reviewers are all underpaid and overworked interns. If this paragraph isn't cut, then that means my gamble paid off!
(The article is signed with a hand-written capital "K".)

name: The End of The World Is Upon Us!?
content:
Author: Lana Smithee

Griffin City's conspiracy theorists are about to be disappointed, as the missing Prime Minister Dorothy has already contacted our firm to state that she was neither threatened or kidnapped, but our readers who hoped for absolute pandemonium should not despair too soon, because after that, the Prime Minister made a joint statement to Griffin City with Stella Hoshii, who sparked the large-scale disturbance earlier, announcing that the end of the world is coming and asked everyone to back up their memories.

Despite using the Parapluie virus to assault today's protest, Stella Hoshii is now standing side by side with Prime Minister Dorothy. Is what they call the "end of the world" going to be a doomsday in the traditional sense, like hurricanes, snowstorms, torrential rains, floods, or even asteroid impacts? Or is there some other hidden meaning to it?

When interviewed, Griffin City resident Gr MP5 said, "It's not like there's anything to be scared about, it's only the end of the world." "Only the natives with one life should be worried." Another citizen, Viking, added.

name: A Letter To The Commander
content:
Dear Commander of Griffin:
Hey, happy Southern Hemisphere… Alright, Alma said I needed to greet you properly, so I specially came over here to do as the Romans do, hah.
They insisted that I give you a proper greeting, and I think now is the right time for it. First, I'd like to thank you and Miss Kalina for allowing us to stay here. What I'm saying is that I'm very happy… After all, Griffin is an excellent place, with ample drink ingredients, and Miss Kalina is also very passionate, although all her contracts (where does she get them all from?) are written in very...thought-provoking language. Still, I'm sure that we'll be able to get along happily with all the humans and Dolls here, as well as to get them drunk.
Also, please forget the name registered on my contract and call me Jill.  J — I — L — L Jill, Please. Remember. That. Finally, I wish you and your family members good health, and that we'll enjoy our new lives. If you'd like to have some time for mixing drinks and changing lives, you know I'll be in the Cafe.

—Jill Stingray

Dear Commander, 
 Thanks so much for taking care of me. Here's a small gift. I hope you'll like it, and good luck with your work today!

Photo From Christmas 2018
content:
Commander:
Turkey! Apple pie! Spending this festive holiday with this joyous and warm feeling with everyone here will surely become precious memories for all of us.
I've sent you a secretly taken photo of Miss Suomi~ She is sooo cute! Also, I look forward to your continued patronage, Commander~

name: Christmas Special Kvass Tank
content:
Dear Commander:

Those Northern Eurasian T-Dolls said they needed to use a special vehicle to carry the alcohol... I was shocked when they brought this thing out! I think even the humans probably have already forgotten about this tradition... Yet, they said that "this bit of alcohol is only enough for tonight!" Anyways, the most important thing during Christmas is to make everyone happy, so...I'm sure you wouldn't mind them turning storage tanks into barrels for the alcohol, right?

name: Memories From Christmas 2018
content:
Dear Commander:

Miss Springfield was busy in the kitchen for the whole day preparing for the banquet. She had also prepared a big bag of gifts and wanted to act as Santa... I didn't think she and the other T-Dolls would be so enthusiastic about this holiday. I'm sure it's because you're here with everybody. I hope that next year, no, every future Christmas will be like tonight! I wish you a prosperous future as well!

name: Gifts-Filled Banquet Hall
content:
Dear Commander:

We've finally finished setting up the banquet hall for Christmas! Let's take a picture as a commemoration before the T-Dolls come rushing in. Although, I only noticed something was off after we finished setting everything up…but for the sake of the festive spirit, I think everyone else will like it very much!

name: Dormouse of Halloween 2018
content:
Commander:

Did you know the day we call "Halloween" is actually the eve of the true Halloween? The actual "Halloween" is November 1st. According to records, it is to celebrate all the saints of a certain religion...so on the night before the actual Halloween, dressing up is supposed to ward off bad spirits? So what exactly is it supposed to be...? Anyways, you can't go wrong with celebrating and having fun!

name: One-of-a-Kind Treasure of Halloween 2018
content:
Commander:

Hold onto this photo for me! If "V" finds out... No, nevermind, it's nothing. You'd better not throw it out! I promise you it's not a cursed photo that's going to attract demons. If anything, it would ~only~ attract fire bombs~

name: Gift of Halloween 2018
content:
Dear Commander:

I don't know if you'll like this gift, but you usually adopt a lot of pets so I think you'll also like her. That's right, she's a girl, and she loves to follow people around! Don't be scared of her appearance, though~
Oh, almost forgot to mention, don't sleep in the same room with her. It'll be really difficult to hire another commander... Just joking!

name: Commemoration of Halloween 2018
content:
Dear Commander:

The lively festival is over. Are you going to miss it? Everyone had a lot of fun and it was great! All the strange events that happened on this evening had been recorded down in a notebook. It's not going to end up being cursed, right? Hahaha, just kidding! I'm sure we'll have more stories in the future, won't we, Commander?

name: Photo From the Site of the Attack
content:
Dear Commander:

Thank you for your hard work! Who would've thought that so many things could happen during an ordinary day at the opera theatre. However, having gone through this incident, I think you've become a little closer with everyone! 
By the way, I noticed a very unique photograph while going through the evidence...and I thought that you might've wanted to keep it, so I made a copy for you. Those small injuries Thompson received in the battle makes her look even cooler in this photo!

name: A Certain Someone's Customized Motorcycle
content: Miss AEK said before the mission today that the Commander might need it, so she sent her motorcycle here. It sure looks cool... I wanna give it a test ride myself. What do you think, Commander?

name: Gift From the Theatre
content: Things have finally come to an end, and we had received the theatre's thanks. All's well that ends well. But it sure is a gorgeous theatre... Too bad I can only look at it through pictures. I'm so jealous of the Commander! I definitely want to see an opera there in my lifetime, so I'm going to start saving up for it from now on!

name: Year of Memories Reward 1
content:
Dear Commander:
This Eastern festival is really fantastic, isn't it? Not only are there delicious foods, you also get money...*cough cough*. Anyways, we all spent an unforgettable holiday together. By the way, this is a close-up photo of tonight's "Goddess of Red Packets". As expected of the person that was giving out money to leave the deepest impressions. Miss Gd DSR-50 really knew how to pick her role in this event. Ahem, let's forget about the money thing for a second... This is a special reward for organizing the festival. Please accept it, Commander~

name: Year of Memories Reward 2
content:
Dear Commander:
I was completely shocked when I first saw the banquet hall! This blend of Eastern and Western styles totally transformed our base's barroom. This style is quite chic, isn't it? That's why I'm leaving it this way~ Consider this a special reward for this holiday season!

name: Year of Memories Reward 3
content:
Dear Commander:
The event organizers were really dazzling tonight... Ah, especially Miss Gd DSR-50; all eyes were on her! I regret not joining the organizers team... I could've gotten a new costume too... By the way, this picture was taken at the end of the banquet. Miss Gd DSR-50 is really beautiful, although it seems like she drank a bit too much... This kind of shooting opportunity is hard to come by, so please take good care of this photo~

name: Honey Sweet Moment Reward - Melancholic Bride
content: A picture of an expression that does not seem to match her attire. It is exactly this sense of dissonance that makes this photo worth saving.

name: Honey Sweet Moment Reward - Elite N.E.E.T. Sign
content: Another sign that reveals the true purpose of life. But is this "truth" reality?

name: Honey Sweet Moment Reward - Wedding Curtains
content: Seeing the bouquets on the curtains reminds you of that sweet moment, even if it is filled with happiness that is not your own.

name: Honey Sweet Moment Reward - Cathedral
content: You can't help but be serious when you enter this solemn building. The promises made here may be the sincerest of them all.

name: Anniversary Party - Anniversary Special Kalina
content: The year together with the Commander was really fun! Please continue to spend just as much next year~

name: Anniversary Party - Steel Giant
content: A painting that looks as if it's world famous. It gives you a heavy feeling in your heart every time you look at it...

name: Anniversary Party - Our Year Together
content: Remember, this edited photo must never be shown to certain important people that were cut out from the left side of the image.

name: Unstealable Gems - Gems Agent
content: Experienced agents will always don an identity before their mission. An exquisitely crafted calling card is also a symbol of professionalism.

name: Unstealable Gems - Time Throne
content: There is no such thing as an eternal throne. Power is like fine sand; it will leak from your grasp bit by bit.

name: Unstealable Gems - The Perfect Exchange
content: Both the buyer and the seller will show a contented smile after the fulfillment of their wishes.

name: Maid Training Camp - Aristocrat's Taste Test
content: ...Well, I finally made a half decent cup of tea. How does it taste, Commander?

name: Maid Training Camp - Maid Internship
content:
Although they can't provide as perfect of an experience as a real maid cafe...
being able to see this side of them here is still worth the price.

name: Maid Training Camp - Cozy Cafe
content: Regardless if you're a human or a T-Doll, feel free to drop by and relax whenever you're worn out.

name: Baywatch Unlock Reward - Beach Party
content: The T-Dolls at Griffin are unexpectedly given a short and peaceful summer vacation, but the beach might be more than what it seems... Will the T-Dolls really be able to enjoy this "peaceful" vacation?

name: Baywatch Unlock Reward - Beach Punk 2064
content: Gr G41! Here we go! Please watch my performance, Master!

name: Baywatch Unlock Reward - Fel in Diving Suit
content: To commemorate the adventures on the beach, Fel got a new outfit... Not sure when it's gonna come in useful, but FAL's happy about it, and that's what matters!

name: Candy Pocket
content: The original purpose of the tactical bag was to allow everyone to bring more disposable equipment for their missions, but everyone just uses it to store their favorite treats.

name: Extra Parts
content: The Commander asked everyone to carry some spare parts for the occasional need, but this would increase their load, so the T-Dolls devised a method to solve their problem.

name: Worrywart
content: The more things you know, the more worries you'll have. However, anxiety is a useless thing, and the only thing we can do is our best.

name: Lovestruck
content: Cake, chocolate, or a love letter... What did you receive today? Or did you receive them all? You can't let the others find out if you're really receiving them!

name: Overthinking
content: Too many things on your mind will make you unable to concentrate. Therefore, it's a good strategy to distract yourself before you start thinking too much. Helian's suggestion is to take on more missions, and Kalina's suggestion is to go shopping with her as much as possible.

name: Cherry Blossom Breeze
content: Flowers blossoming in spring, new clothes, the ground covered in soft grass... Although one can only dream of such things these days, the sense of peace they bring can carry over to reality.

name: Stormy Cloud
content: Be tolerant. Put yourself in other people's shoes. Try to understand others... But right now I don't want to think about anything. I just want to vent my feelings without a care in the world.

name: Oncoming Storm
content: Even if we know we're in the wrong, it can still be hurtful when we get told off. Living with negative emotions and learning to correct our mistakes are a part of growing up, but...ugh...I can't bear it anymre...

name: Furniture: Current - Command Center
content: The source of all battle commands. The Commander's main workplace.

name: Furniture: Current - HQ Intelligence Center
content: The main intelligence center. A vault of Griffin's most valuable asset.

name: Furniture: Current - HQ Data Room
content: The place where intelligence is screened and processed. Miss Kalina has spent most of her precious youth here.

name: Furniture: Current - Special Reception
content: Entry to this mysterious little room is forbidden for Griffin Dolls, and it seems uninhabited, but every now and then footsteps can be heard from it in the middle of the night…

name: Furniture: Current - Frontline Intelligence Center
content: A branch of the Frontline Combat Team - true elites understand the importance of intelligence.

name: Furniture: Current - Frontline Basecamp
content: The basecamp of the Frontline Combat Team. The final stop before an operation begins.

name: Furniture: Current - Frontline Depot
content: The depot of the Frontline Combat Team. Most of the things stored in here aren't meant for the public eye.

name: Furniture: Current - Response Intelligence Center
content: A branch of the Response Combat Team - so much intel is gathered here it could work nine Kalinas to death.

name: Furniture: Current - Response Basecamp
content: The basecamp of the Response Combat Team. The atmosphere isn't too cold and deadly here...in fact, it's quite laid-back.

name: Furniture: Current - Response Depot
content: The depot of the Response Combat Team. Unimaginable things are stored here - because it literally has EVERYTHING.

name: Furniture: Current - Border Intelligence Center
content: A branch of the Border Surveillance Corps - mainly specializing in producing topographical images and diagrams. Do you like maps?

name: Furniture: Current - Border Basecamp
content: Forward Basecamp, where echoes can be heard - no matter where you are, we'll be right behind you.

name: Furniture: Current - Border Depot
content: The depot of the Border Surveillance Corps. Holy crap, you guys are even messier than the Response Combat Team!

name: Furniture: Current - Support Intelligence Center
content: A branch of the General Support Team - the branch we're most familiar with and the source of most intel missions.

name: Furniture: Current - Fairy Chamber
content: I repeat - those are not toys! Don't make me say that again!

name: Furniture: Current - Garage
content: A hangout for the HOCs. Probably the place that resembles a military camp the most…

name: Furniture: Current - Protocol Control Center
content: We don't know much about this stuff… Perhaps our enemies have more insight.

name: Furniture: Current - Special Training Ground
content: A new training ground especially built for the Assimilated Forces. They value their privacy.

name: Furniture: Current - Isolated Testing Ground
content: "What, you want to come with us?"

name: Furniture: Current - Specialized Factory
content: It isn't exactly special treatment… We just use different tech.

name: Furniture: Current - Café
content: Everyone likes a drink after a mission, but sometimes someone else comes along to fill in for Miss Springfield. I just hope I never run into such occasions.

name: Furniture: Current - Dormitory
content: "Commander… No more than three. We can't take care of any more."

name: Furniture: Current - Repair Bay
content: "Don't look at me! They said no more than three!"

name: Furniture: Current - Cafeteria
content: The most human-like feature of Tactical Dolls is that they never let good food go to waste - though the list of Dolls banned from the kitchen is getting longer and longer.

name: Furniture: Current - Supply Warehouse
content: This is Griffin's largest as well as tidiest warehouse, managed by Miss Kalina herself.

name: Furniture: Current - Secretary Office
content: Miss Kalina's private office - What? So the Data Room isn't her office?

name: Furniture: Current - Banquet Hall
content: A big hall reserved for large-scale events. Several Dolls also hang out here in their free time - but no drinking competitions!

name: Furniture: Current - Club Activity Room
content: Dolls find leisure and entertainment here, but you can always see a few familiar faces in this room - "MDR, you're slacking off again!"

name: Icon: Concert Ticket
content: It may not amount to much at the moment, but one day, it will shine.

name: Furniture：Debut Poster
content: No matter how much time has passed, they will always remember that moment - when they stood on the stage with their dreams, uncertainty, and passion. All the effort was worth it.

name: ID: Gilded Name Card
content: You may not be particularly famous, but your name cards should still be exquisite because you never know when your fans will covet these original special-edition cards and make expensive bids for them.

name: Top Decoration: Concert Lightstick
content: Superiors aren't expected to support their subordinates in pursuing their dreams, but if you're willing to do that...

name: Besties Chatter: Morning Star
content:
Unlock the gossip of the girls as they are preparing for a group photo.
After completing the correct setup for the group photo, return to the Base Screen to listen to it.

name: 【Furniture】Master of Fate
content:
Trust your destiny and be the master of fate. Even if you can't roll a 6, at least roll something less pathetic than a 1.
 "Glory be to Griffin."

name: 【Special Effects】Cards of Unpredictability
content:
Given how unpredictable fate is, no one can tell if the next card will help you turn the tables.
 "If I can't draw a good card, I'll just print one myself."

name: 【Furniture】Master of Wealth
content:
Take the money out of your pockets and be the master of wealth. If you can't do that, you will be its slave instead and toil your life away.
 "...Why are you all staring at me?" - Kalina

name: 【Icon】Icon: King of Tricks
content:
"You're incredible! Practically invincible!"
 "No wait, nothing is invincible. I've remained victorious this whole time because I firmly believe that."

name: 【ID card】Royal Flush
content: If you have a good hand, pretend you don't; if you don't have a good hand, pretend you do.

name: Commander Headwear: Nova Cap
content: There were once a group of people who let children dream of the stars and taught them about loss and cherishing what they had.

name: Furniture: Outer Polaris
content: A promotional poster for a movie when it was first shown in the theaters. Some people say it's a movie that portrays the reality of being an astronomer, while others say it's a romance disguised as soft sci-fi.

name: ID: Polaris Light
content: These bright memories will never fade, and neither will her autograph on this poster.

name: Furniture: Perfect Tea Party
content: The best barista + The best pâtissier = A perfect tea party.

name: Top Decoration: Spare Headband
content: One of G36's trusty work items. She never makes any wasted effort, and seeks only the slightest sense of ceremony.

name: ID: Work Checklist
content: Perhaps she possesses a pocket watch that lets her be in three places at once... and perhaps the Commander should cut down on adventure novels featuring a certain rascal trio.

name: Icon: Spring
content: Her emotions are unlike that of the passing seasons, yet they tug at your heartstrings ever so insistently.

name: Return, Triumph of Griffin!
content:
Welcome back, Commander!
Haven't seen you much lately, I'm sure you've been busy with somethin' more important, but we hope you'd still come and check in on us every once in a while.
You can now try out lots of new work, and our new T-Dolls are dyin' to meet you.
Please accept this gift, and let us embark on our journey once more!

name: Returning Support from My Other Wing!
content:
Commander <color=#ffb400>#playername</color> has returned to the battlefield and thank you for your support!
Let's watch each other's back and work hard together from now on!
*Returning Support Reward can only be collected once.

Witch's Forest Unlock Reward - Pumpkin Skewers
content: S.A.T.8, a T-Doll who constantly slides back and forth between being unperturbed and being dead serious, what could possibly have pushed her to the far end on the other side of her neural cloud's scales this time?

name: Witch's Forest Unlock Reward - Ghost Trap, Counterattack!
content: Is this the biggest pinch that the Invincible No. 1 Netizen MDR has ever faced? Who could have done something so...amusing? (MDR: delete plz)

name: Witch's Forest Unlock Reward - Witch's Forest Wallpaper
content: This picture was taken during a private Griffin Halloween party. That night...all the Dolls in the picture...changed back to their regular clothes.

name: Witch's Forest Unlock Reward - Guns N' Side Boxes
content: Is this merely a festive costume, or is it the real monster that I am? I'm like the side boxes on your motorcycle. You don't see me, but I'm always looking at you...as you travel to your next destination...

name: Christmas Eve Express Unlock Reward - Little Elf Night Light
content: This snowflake-styled Christmas night light, found in a world that seeks to warm you with all its heart this winter -- Commander, would you like to add a cute Doll's smile to it?

name: Christmas Eve Express Unlock Reward - Queen of X'mas Morning
content: The T-Doll who managed to seize all sales and discounts on Christmas Eve. Despite her tender smile, her past is the most un-silent secret on this Silent Night.

name: Christmas Eve Express Unlock Reward - Scarlet Turbo
content: If Christmas is the day when happiness is delivered to everyone, then why does it matter who you are? In any case, she's definitely the T-Doll with the most happiness!

name: Christmas Eve Express Unlock Reward - Bustling X'mas House
content: No Christmas can be celebrated in peace, but the clamor signifies our reunion. A bit of conflict only serves to bring more warmth to this little house.

name: Operation New Year Visit Unlock Reward - Bionic Pig Charger
content: This bionic pig-shaped mobile charger can quickly charge T-Dolls and has many adaptors to handle various circumstances... "Adaptors? What do you mean by adaptors?" Gr MP5 asks.

name: Operation New Year Visit Unlock Reward - Door Guardian Window Cutouts
content: A paper cutout that Type95 made after witnessing the events of Chinese New Year Eve. "I won't have two dummies who froze themselves solid on Chinese New Year's Eve as my door guardians! Send them back to where they came from!" Type97 said after seeing it.

name: Operation New Year Visit Unlock Reward - Sangria Succulent
content: "Happy New Year. I hope you will keep it up in the coming year. I'll look forward to your performance."

name: Operation New Year Visit Unlock Reward - Sangria Succulent
content: "Even though it's a joy to share good wine with others, drinking alone from time to time can also be a luxury."

name: Guns N' Roses Unlock Reward - Magic Dressing Table
content: Sufficiently advanced science is indistinguishable from magic. No Doll can resist the magic that makes them beautiful, and so they sit here for long periods of time.

name: Guns N' Roses Unlock Reward - The Most Beautiful Smile
content: The best shot is taken when the owner of the smile feels genuinely happy.

name: Guns N' Roses Unlock Reward - Sweet Selection
content: There is no luck in life, only individual choices. Of course, there are times when you don't want to choose... Then again, choosing everything is also a choice.

name: Guns N' Roses Unlock Reward - Blissful Mission
content: She is the emissary of happiness and hope. Only the person who gives her a mission can see what she really looks like.

name: Night of Sweetness and Surprise - Tactical Stealth Box
content: The contemporary Romeo won't have to climb up a balcony to see Juliet. All he needs to do is put Juliet in this stealth box, and she can elope with him as safely and comfortably as if she were sitting on a train.

name: Night of Sweetness and Surprise - Operation Ball Girl
content: The girls look absolutely stunning on the stage. If there is always such a performance in every random gala, I'd look forward to it even if it is a total farce.

name: Night of Sweetness and Surprise - "Seizing First Place"
content: "T-The bet is on! Even if I come in last, I'll gladly take the punishment!"

name: Operation Mermaid - Custom Orange Kitty Lifeguard
content: A new model of orange lifeguard kitty equipped with cutting-edge gear reports for duty! But who can this frail little kitty save in the vast ocean? It can't even save itself.

name: Operation Mermaid - Summer Memories
content: Though that girl's luck didn't follow her into these waters...being able to capture her leisurely smile might be a sign that her luck went to me instead.

name: Operation Mermaid - Mermaid Stand
content: To alleviate the disappointment of not finding any mermaids, the Commander has ordered a mermaid photo stand made especially for the Dolls. However, Dolls with wide faces probably shouldn't try too hard to shove their head through...

name: Operation Mermaid - R-Type Over-The-Shoulder Throw
content: Huh?! Don't play card games on the beach! Why not try some exciting competitive sports? What exactly...? Heheh, what about this?!

name: Night of the Danse Macabre - "Shall we play a game?"
content: "...Sis? Don't be afraid. There's so much I can do. I can protect you. I can even... Heheh, shall we play a game?"

name: Night of the Danse Macabre - Space Gentledog
content: "I. Super star dancer. Gold farming." "Kalina?! The dog translator you just bought really does work! ...Wait, no! Come and see what kind of scary stuff this dog translator just said!"

name: Night of the Danse Macabre - "No treat, but don't trick"
content: "(Sob) I've been working so hard for these grocery store coupons... You've already tricked me, so why are you scaring me as well?!"

name: Night of the Danse Macabre -Feast of the Monstrous
content: "Night falls. This is when the monstrous creeps out from the shadows within the Griffin compound..." "No, cut! Again! If you don't do this properly, I won't give you your soda or your discount coupons!"

name: Florentine's Gift - X'mas Sock Full of Presents
content: A modest-looking X'mas Sock that contains the well wishes and kindness of countless people - "Which makes this a perfectly safe place to hide," thinks a certain dinergate infiltrating Griffin. Hopefully it will deliver the presents successfully.

name: Florentine's Gift - Vixen User Manual
content: A manual for "Vixen", a mech built especially for Christmas... Even though it can't soar through the sky, it can still deliver your presents! It's really hardworking!

name: Florentine's Gift - Smile of the Mistletoe
content: The beautiful legend about the girl who's pure as snow guarding the mistletoe - in the merciless cold of winter, other than a hot bowl of soup, the girl's smile can also warm you right up.

name: Florentine's Gift - Florentine's X'mas Tree
content: The joy of Christmas isn't about any person, it's about the Christmas tree that was planted to make everyone smile happily... That's the most charming thing about Christmas Night!

name: Blood Moon on Halloween - Legendary Headpieces
Charming Furniture Expo - Sticker of Good Fortune
content: A sticker that bears the Dolls' well-wishing. Someone stuck it on the Commander's door.

name: Charming Furniture Expo - Space Chair
content: This is a miraculous chair. Just sit on it, relax, close your eyes and count to five, then everything will change...

name: Charming Furniture Expo - Whispers in the Candlelight
content: Outside the window is the ceaseless and boisterous sound of exploding firecrackers; inside the house is a sleepless New Year's night. Why not light a candle and have a late-night heart-to-heart with someone you care about?

name: Charming Furniture Expo - New Year Rituals
content: Is there a better New Year gift than waking up from a short nap and finding oneself surrounded by gifts? Right now, the Commander is inclined to answer in the negative.

name: Mystery of the Bewitching Figure - Secret Recorder
content: Things that document the truth are never immediately visible. Guess how many camera heads there are in here?

name: Mystery of the Bewitching Figure - Invaluable True Feelings
content: She is willing to always give you the benefit of the doubt when things happen – this is how she interprets the concept of "trust".

name: Mystery of the Bewitching Figure - Perfect Ending
content: Everything comes to a peaceful resolution on this day. Have you thought about how to respond to all the genuine feelings they have shown you?

name: Mystery of the Bewitching Figure - Witness of the Starry Night
content: As the meteor falls, a pair of eyes are taking in the starry sky – her eyes are much better than RMB-93's camera.

name: Symphony No.4 - Furniture: "Standstill"
content: Though Death has brought me to a halt, please remember me by this... I have lived.

name: Symphony No.4 - Furniture: "Concept"
content: Please, please, please specify if it's a banquet or a party next time you promote an event. There's a huge difference in scale between the two.

name: Symphony No.4 - Icon: "Goal"
content: Do not hesitate, do not be distracted. Try to think – what exactly is your goal?

name: Symphony No.4 - ID: "Debate"
content: Impossible! My way is definitely better! I'm calling for a vote on the forum! —Zas M76
